Question :- 1

Why should the product's data be passed through navigation arguments rather thanre-fetching it from the server on the detail screen? Describe the Flutter approach you would use,and explain one trade-off this introduces when the product object includes a large array of
images or variant options


Ans :-

The product's data should be passed through navigation arguments instead of re-fetching it from the server because it improves performance and provides a better user experience.
Since the product information is already available on the home screen, 
passing it directly avoids an unnecessary network request, reduces loading time, saves bandwidth, and allows the detail screen to open instantly. 
It also works better when the device has a slow or unstable internet connection.

Trade-off

A disadvantage of passing the entire product object is that it may contain large arrays of images or variant options,
increasing memory usage and making navigation slower because a large amount of data is transferred between screens.
It can also make the app less efficient if the object is very large.
